<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Import your Wallet</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style4.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <a href="#" class="back-link">&larr; Back</a>
        <h1>Import your Wallet</h1>
        <div class="tabs">
            <button class="tab active">Recovery Phrase</button>
            <button class="tab">Private Key</button>
        </div>
        <div class="recovery-phrase">
            <div class="phrase-inputs">
                <div class="row">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="1">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="7">
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="2">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="8">
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="3">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="9">
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="4">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="10">
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="5">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="11">
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="6">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="12">
                </div>
            </div>
            <button class="paste-btn">Paste from clipboard</button>
            <button class="import-btn">Import</button>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
            <img src="ronin-info.png" alt="Ronin Info" class="info-img">
            <div class="info-text">
                <h2>What is a Recovery Phrase?</h2>
                <p>It is a 12-word phrase that can be used to restore your wallet.</p>
                <h2>Does Ronin Wallet support Recovery Phrases generated by other wallets?</h2>
                <p>Yes, Ronin Wallet currently supports all EVM-compatible 12-word Recovery Phrases generated by Metamask, Trust, Coinbase Wallet, etc.</p>
                <h2>Is it safe to enter it into Ronin Wallet?</h2>
                <p>Yes. It will be stored locally and never leave your device without your explicit permission.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
